https://www.reddit.com/r/developersIndia/comments/1fvw42s/interview_preparatory_material_for_cracking_google/

=> Week 1: Object-Oriented Programming Refresher
- Focus on: Abstraction, Inheritance, Polymorphism, Encapsulation, SOLID principles
- Low Level Design Primer Course by sudoCode - https://lnkd.in/dXWmSAac
- Neetcode OOP Design Interviews and Patterns - https://neetcode.io/
- Object-Oriented Design in Python (top-rated & structured) - https://lnkd.in/d_NAQxgE

=> Week 2: Design Patterns (Foundations)
- Focus on: Singleton, Factory, Strategy, Observer, and Decorator
- Design Patterns (Low Level) Youtube Playlist - https://lnkd.in/dbzfbmkE
- Newsletter: ByteByteGo for real-world examples - https://lnkd.in/d5EUiyUk
- Blog: Refactoring Guru — OOP Basics & SOLID Principles - https://lnkd.in/dz6RzydD
- Ebook: "Head First Design Patterns" (freely available pdf on Github)

=> Week 3: Start Building — Design Real Systems
- Pick 3 Systems: Elevator, ATM, and Parking Lot
- Focus on: Class diagrams, Interfaces, UMLs
- YouTube: Gaurav Sen Low Level Design Examples Playlist - https://lnkd.in/d5bY5f2Y

=> Week 4: Practice More Use Cases
- Pick More Systems: Design BookMyShow, Splitwise, and Tic-Tac-Toe
- Focus On: Extensibility, Modularity, Separation of Concerns
- Low Level Design Roadmap by Shrayanash (some videos are in Hindi) - https://lnkd.in/dWK6yq8b

=> Week 5: Design at Scale & Mock Interviews
- Peer-to-peer reviews, thinking under pressure
- Interview Low Level Design Interview Questions - https://lnkd.in/dPMqcQgc
- YouTube: Scaler LLD mock sessions
- Join Discord/Slack groups or practice with friends

=> Week 6: Project & Review Week
- Pick a mini-capstone project (e.g., Cab Booking System or Food Delivery)
- Deliver: Class diagrams, APIs, clean architecture
- Share on LinkedIn for feedback + visibility
- Revisit patterns where you struggled

=> Checkpoint Every Sunday:
- Did I finish the week’s targets?
- Are my class diagrams clean?
- Did I revise what I learned?
- Can I explain the system and trade-offs neatly to a 5-year-old?

Pro Tip: You can’t watch your way into being good at LLD. You’ve got to do the reps. => 

- Design on paper
- Discuss with friends
- Post your learnings
